metadata.name: Room of Imagination #20
metadata.description:
"Is this the real life?

Is this just fantasy?"

Room of Imagination is an exercise of fantasy, where a room of our creative mind comes true.

The colors and elements convey sensations and the final result conveys the feeling.


The Rooms of Imagination are layered artworks generated from a pool of previously rendered digital furniture.

attributes.name: What am i going to do today?

metadata.name: Phantoms #202
metadata.description:
Phantoms is a series of hazy memories of distant places. Some tranquil, others sinister, each scene is as much defined by what is revealed as by what remains unseen.

In this collection I aim to juxtapose hard and soft. Blocky shapes form the core of the compositions. Upon these surfaces, soft textures appear to flow and drip over the sides. Varying levels of opacity, lighting, and fog effects further soften the scenes to create an atmospheric, dream-like quality. By remaining semi-abstract, each of the color palettes are given the space to influence the mood dramatically.

metadata.name: Unicorn #9090
metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. metadata.name: Dynamic generations #205
metadata.description:
A classic cellular automata updates its state with a static rule based on the state of its neighbor.

This collection was created with cellular automata with an extension of that idea. Here the state and the rule are updated based on the state of its neighbor, here the rule changes in every iteration, here the rule is dynamic.

That change moves cellular automata to another level of complexity.

metadata.name: Saturday Night's Alright (For Fighting) #48
metadata.description:
Ok, this is just for fun!
An NFT that changes every day based on the browser weekday.

The preview is generated accordingly, hence it will be different based on the day of the mint.

Control Keys:
- 0 -> Sunday
- 1 -> Monday
- 2 -> Tuesday
- 3 -> Wednesday
- 4 -> Thursday
- 5 -> Friday
- 6 -> Saturday!
- S -> save png
- H -> save high res png
